FBIS4-13572 "drnes077_r_94007" FBIS-NES-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 India PRC Envoy Rules Out Beijing's Mediation on Kashmir PRC Envoy Rules Out Beijing's Mediation on Kashmir BK2004150594 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 GMT 20 Apr 94 BK2004150594 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] China says India and Pakistan should find a solution to the Kashmir issue bilaterally. The Chinese ambassador in India, Mr. Cheng Ruisheng, told a press conference in Calcutta this afternoon that China does not want to be a mediator on the issue. On nonproliferation, Mr. Ruisheng said no country should pressurize India to sign the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty. Replying to a question on India's new economic policy, he said the time has come to integrate developing economies with the world economy to expedite progress.
